  "No significant benefits because people will still choose to drive in accordance with classical theory": "",
  "Only economic benefits for local businesses, particularly regarding better under the given assumptions": "",
  "The 15-minute city provides multi-dimensional sustainability benefits: fewer vehicle miles traveled and emissions, better air quality, improved physical health from active transportation, stronger community bonds, lower infrastructure costs, and less land devoted to vehicle infrastructure.": "",
  "A city's complete streets program redesigns a four-lane road into a two-lane road with protected bike lanes, widened sidewalks, street trees, and a bus-only lane. Business owners initially fear losing customers due to reduced car lanes. One year later, pedestrian traffic is up 40%, cycling has tripled, bus ridership increased 25%, and retail sales have grown. What does this outcome illustrate about sustainable transportation planning?": "",
