  "Reducing car lanes always decreases economic activity in commercial areas": "",
  "Only the bus ridership increase mattered; other changes were irrelevant": "",
  "This outcome shows that well-designed complete streets can boost local economic activity by making areas more inviting for pedestrians who browse and shop, while also reducing emissions, improving air quality, encouraging physical activity, and enhancing transit efficiency.": "",
  "Two identical office buildings are constructed side by side. Building X has a conventional dark roof, standard windows, no green infrastructure, and relies on underground parking. Building Y has a green roof, high-performance windows, bioswales in the parking area, rooftop solar, and a bike parking facility. During a summer heat wave followed by a heavy rainstorm, how would their performance differ?": "",
